<big style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">CRISPR
Recognition Tool</span></big><br style="font-family: arial;">
<small><br style="font-family: arial;">
<span style="font-weight: bold; font-family: arial;">Current version</span><span
 style="font-family: arial;">:&nbsp; 1.1&nbsp; (March 14, 2007)</span></small><small><span
 style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>
Operating System</span>:&nbsp; Platform independent</span></small><small><span
 style="font-family: arial;"></span></small><small><span
 style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>
License</span>:&nbsp; Public domain software</span></small><small><br>
</small><small><span style="font-family: arial;"><span
 style="font-weight: bold;">Requirements</span>:&nbsp; Java Runtime
Environment (JRE), which is probably on your machine.&nbsp; Currently,
CRT only supports FASTA file format.<br>
<br>
</span></small>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;"><small><span
 style="font-family: arial;"><br style="font-family: arial;">
</span></small><small><span
 style="font-weight: bold; font-family: arial;">Graphical User
Interface (GUI)<br>
<br>
Instructions</span><span style="font-family: arial;">: <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Download <a href="CRT1.1_exe.zip">CRT1.1_exe.zip</a>
and unzip the file to a folder.&nbsp; (The extracted file should be
named CRT1.1_exe.jar)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Double-click the extracted file.&nbsp; (Or, at the
command line type:&nbsp; java -jar CRT1.1_exe.jar)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Please, click <a href="compile_from_source.html">here</a>
if the above instructions do not work.</span></small><small><span
